First class: Andreia Blanchard '81, Dick Culler, Karen Curtis McConico '98, Bob Davidson '55, Otis Foster '78, Gene Littles '69, Brian Payne '93, Jerry Steele (athletic director 1972-1998, basketball coach 31 seasons 1972-2003).

### NCAA Tournament wins (rare; cite when relevant)
Women's lacrosse: May 12, 2017, beat #18 Towson 21-15 (first ever). Volleyball: April 14, 2021 (over Central Florida). Men's soccer: Nov 17, 2022 (over North Carolina). Baseball: June 1, 2024 (10-9 over Vanderbilt).

## Religious Life

### Voice traits
Warmer, more reflective, less promotional. Less exclamation, more "join us." Methodist-rooted, open to all faiths, with strong Catholic and Jewish programming.

### Programs
- Weekly Chapel worship (Wednesdays 5:30 pm at Hayworth Chapel)
- HPU Sunday (student-led evening worship, Sundays 8 pm)
- Catholic Mass (Sundays 6 pm at Hayworth Chapel)
- Communion (Thursdays 11:30 am at Hayworth Chapel)
- HPU Hillel and Office of Jewish Life (Shabbat dinners, Hanukkah dinner at 1924 PRIME, Passover Seder, Mezuzah Making, challah making, sukkah decoration)
- Catholic Campus Ministry
- Multifaith Prayer and Meditation Space (in Hayworth Hall)
- Interfaith United (hosts annual Iftar)
- Mission trips and spiritual pilgrimages

### People and groups
Rev. Dr. Preston Davis, Minister to the University. Chapel Choir, Genesis Gospel Choir, Collision Worship Band. Board of Stewards. HPU Chamber Singers (Veterans Day "America the Beautiful").

### Core values phrasing
"Belonging, Becoming, and Beholding". The three named values of the Religious Life Office.

