- **Kenneth F. Kahn** (FL). Kenneth F. Kahn School of Law
- **Dr. Rick Workman** (IL; Founder of Heartland Dental). Workman School of Dental Medicine
- **Doug Witcher** '77 (CA and NC; Founder and CEO of Smart Choice). Douglas S. Witcher School of Humanities and Behavioral Sciences ($20 million)
- **Teresa Caine** (NC). Teresa B. Caine School of Nursing

Earlier major facility donors: Earl Congdon, Fred Wilson (Congdon Hall). David and Christy Cottrell (Cottrell Hall, Cottrell Japanese Garden). David Griffin Jr. of D.H. Griffin Company (Twin Towers steel for American Flag Display).

## Traditions

- **Honor Code signing** during Welcome Week (signed on a 6-by-8-foot document)
- **Opening Convocation blanket** (each freshman receives a blanket from Qubein, encouraged to give it to a family member or mentor who provided support)
- **Building bikes for kids** on Move-In Sunday (freshmen build 150 bikes; first day of classes, they surprise local kids by delivering them)
- **First-year book donation** (incoming students donate a favorite childhood book to local elementary/middle schools via Amazon wish list)
- **Bald eagle Clark** soars at Convocation and Commencement
- **Veterans Day blankets** (150+ volunteers give blankets to each veteran)
- **Star of Service and Sacrifice** (veterans sign; displayed on campus)
- **Family Weekend** (parents visit in fall)
- **Annual Veterans Day Celebration** (2,000+ vets; "America the Beautiful" by Chamber Singers)
- **Roasted corn on Earth Day**
- **Halloween and Valentine's Day chocolate from President Qubein** (he passes it out personally)

